data.name: richTextBox2.Text
data.value:
Press F-11 while in game
Server Admin Command List:
sudo help sudo admin [admin_password] login to admin mode. sudo kick [user_name] [kick_reason] kick specific user (reason is optional). sudo ban [user_name] [minutes] [opt. ban_reason] ban specific player (0-minutes for permanent ban) sudo unban [user_name] unban specific player. sudo warn [user_name] warn specific player. sudo maxwarn [number_of_warnings] set max number of warnings. sudo banlist view list of banned players. sudo userlist view list of connected players. sudo pass set password protection for server. sudo nopass remove password protection from the server sudo end_round end playing session. sudo friendlyfire [1/0] enable friendly fire. sudo autoteambalance [1/0] enable team auto-balance. sudo tklimit [number_of_kills] change team kill tolerance level. sudo hostname [new_host_name] change server name. sudo timelimit [minutes] change session time. sudo say_all [message] send admin message to all players. sudo say_player [user_name] [message] send admin message to specific player. sudo map? view levels list. sudo map [mission_type] [level_name] change map by level name. # Yoni note: mission_type is string, from "sudo map?" sudo map# [mission_type] [level_number] change map by level list index. sudo pause pause session. sudo unpause unpause session.

data.name: richTextBox3.Text
data.value:
Add this to shortcut/batch that runs RisingEagle.exe Yoni: Didn't find anything similar for DedicatedServer...
RisingEagle Nebula2 viewer (C) 2004 Frontline Studios Invasion Interactive Ltd - Rising Eagle Command line args: ------------------ -help show this help -startup startup script to run, default is: home:bin/startup.tcl -sceneserver scene server to use -scriptserver script server to use -input input binding script to run, default is: home:bin/stdinput.tcl -view data to load and view with the lighting setup specified (either -stage or the default) -stage light stage to load, default is: home:bin/stdlight.tcl -fullscreen if present, then nviewer will go fullscreen -alwaysontop present the window will be allways on top -w width of window to open (default: 640) -h height of window to open (default: 480) -x the x position of the window (default: 0) -y y position of the window (default: 0) -connect if presents, client will try to connect to specified by "ip:port" server -pass specifies server password (optional) -login if presents, the application will try to login to this account "username,password" -safemode runs in safe mode -projdir the optional project directory (assigns it to the projdir: alias, for use in the user's scripts)
-noautoupdate
